<TEXT>
Mitsubishi is cutting up to 1,000 jobs in Illinois and California, under a
Major restructuring plan.
That's about 20% of Mitsubishi's U.S. workforce.
They will be eliminated in <TIMEX2 val="P2Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1998" anchor_dir="STARTING" comment="">the next two years</TIMEX2>.
The Japanese automaker will also reduce the number of models it <TIMEX2 val="PRESENT_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1998-11-06T11:47:00.24" anchor_dir="AS_OF" comment="">now</TIMEX2> offers
by 40%.
These moves come, as Mitsubishi reports heavy losses for <TIMEX2 val="1998-H1" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="Probably 1999 fiscal year.">the first half of
this year</TIMEX2>.
Mitsubishi says it's been hit hard by the economic crisis in Asia and a
Sharp drop in car sales in Japan.
